correctness.rationale: Significant factual and schema issues across both processes. Key problems: (1) Schema violations and nulls: many required numeric fields are null/None (pressure.quantityValue.numericValue; thicknessControl.growthPerCycle.values[*].value.quantityValue.numericValue; thicknessControl.numberofCycles.quantityValue.numericValue; nucleationPeriod.quantityValue.numericValue; purgeTime[*].*.quantityValue.numericValue; flowRates[*].*.quantityValue.numericValue; opticalProperties.*.quantityValue.numericValue; uniformity.variation.quantityValue.numericValue; conformality.aspectRatio.quantityValue.numericValue; filmDensity.value.quantityValue.numericValue; deviceProperties.many). plasmaPower is provided as null (type object expected). An extra processParameters.filmThickness key (outside thicknessControl) violates additionalProperties: false. (2) Dosing-time and unit errors: Article reports pulse times in seconds; schema requires milliseconds. Values were entered as 4, 8, 0.5 ms instead of 4000, 8000, 500 ms. Times were also incorrectly assigned to precursor doses, which are not supported by the text (the stated changes pertain to ozone). For Ga2O3 in the unsaturated case, co-reactant should be 8 s (8000 ms), but 8 ms was used. (3) Electrical properties misinterpretation: Sheet resistance (Ω/sq) was incorrectly recorded as bulk resistivity (Ω·m). Carrier concentrations from Hall were reported in cm^-3 but not converted to m^-3, and the unit was set to C-PER-M3 instead of PER-M3 (e.g., 4.3e18 cm^-3 should be 4.3e24 m^-3). (4) Device metrics: Unsaturated threshold voltage is wrong (entered −1.04 V vs −0.04 V in the article). (5) Composition: atomicRatio set to “1:1:1” conflates the supercycle subcycle ratio with elemental atomic ratio; XPS in Table I does not support 1:1:1. ElementalConcentration includes only In at.% (9.39% or 8.2%) without Ga and Zn, making it incomplete and not reflective of the film composition reported. (6) Unsupported/speculative entries: otherAspects.filmStability and reproducibility set to True without textual support; multiple fields filled with “Not Found” placeholders reduce traceability. Corrections needed: remove or populate all null numeric fields (omit optional properties rather than set nulls); fix dosing times (convert s→ms, apply only to ozone where stated); correct electrical properties (do not use sheet resistance as resistivity; convert carrier density to PER-M3); correct V_TH for the unsaturated device to −0.04 V; update atomic ratio from XPS or adjust to be traceable; remove extraneous processParameters.filmThickness and any properties not defined by the schema.

completeness.rationale: Two IGZO ALD processes (saturated and unsaturated) are captured with correct system type (TALD), precursors (DADI/TMGa/DEZn), oxidant (ozone), substrate (Si(100)), temperature (250 °C), supercycle 1:1:1, amorphous phase, and roughness values (0.24/0.22 nm). However, completeness is poor due to many schema-required fields left null or filled with placeholders and multiple factual/unit errors: (1) DosingTime units and attribution: article reports pulse times in seconds (ozone), but extraction uses MilliSEC without conversion (e.g., 4 s, 8 s entered as 4 ms, 8 ms), and assigns these times also to precursor dosing though the article only specifies ozone; for unsaturated Ga2O3 the ozone pulse remains 8 s but is entered as 8 ms. (2) Pressure numericValue is null; GrowthPerCycle numeric values and numberofCycles are null; PurgeTime, FlowRates contain nulls; NucleationPeriod null; Uniformity.variation and Conformality.aspectRatio null; FilmDensity value null. These violate the ‘no nulls’ schema intent and required fields. (3) Electrical properties: Resistivity is wrongly populated from sheet resistance (should be ~4.5e-4 and 2.7e-4 Ω·m for 10 nm films, not 4.5e4/2.7e4 Ω·m). Carrier density units/values are wrong (should be per m3: 4.3e24 and 2.5e25 m−3; extraction uses 4.3e18/2.5e19 with C-PER-M3). (4) Device threshold voltage for unsaturated film is incorrect (−1.04 V extracted vs −0.04 V reported). (5) Film composition is incomplete and partly incorrect: only In at.% is provided; Ga, Zn, O, C at.% from Table I are missing; ‘atomicRatio’ is set to 1:1:1 (process cycle ratio) but reported XPS atomic fractions are not 1:1:1. (6) Reactor fields and several properties set to “Not Found”/True without article support (e.g., safety, stability, reproducibility). To improve completeness, correct dosing-time units and attribution, compute/enter resistivity and carrier density with correct units, fix V_TH for the unsaturated device, populate full XPS composition (In, Ga, Zn, O, C), and either provide or omit (per schema) fields currently set to null: pressure, growth-per-cycle and cycles, purge/flow details, uniformity and conformality metrics, and film density.
